	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=28999><span id= >Domnall</span></a><br><span id=notbold>198 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Consider this...<br><br>FBSS (21% or 19%, depending on who you talk to)<br>Enchanter Haste (varies as to spell and Enchanter whim, but by this level NEVER below 30% - Augment)<br><br>Most melee characters by 50, Rangers especially, are gonna have some kind of haste item. FBSS is the defacto standard that all the others are measured by, since it is probably one of the easiest to get, or at least most common. Under 50, most are going to hit their haste cap REAL fast, especially if there is a bard on the group.<br><br>As far as comparing Epics, Ranger Epic also has a 40% Haste, coupled with a single target slow for offhand second Epic piece (yes, Rangers actually get two weapons for their Epic). High level Rangers hit their Haste cap really quick (or at least get awfully close to it) if the Enchanter in the group has a Snake Stick.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
